description: In September, GST collections in India witnessed a 6.5% rise to Rs 1,73,240 crore, marking the slowest increase in over three years due to domestic factors. While strong monsoon disruptions affected collections in some states, experts anticipate a boost from festival sales in the coming months, viewing GST revenue as a gauge for economic growth.
title: At 6.5%, GST collection growth slowest in 3 years

description: A granddaughter of Mahatma Gandhi reflects on her experiences with both Gandhi and PM Modi, highlighting the latter's dedication to national issues and development aligned with Gandhi's ideals. She argues that Modi's policies and actions embody the change Gandhi envisioned for India.
title: PM Modi: Living the ideals of Mahatma Gandhi

description: Oil prices surged approximately 4% as tensions escalated with Iran reportedly preparing a missile attack on Israel. This geopolitical distress also caused a significant dip in the S&P 500, with technology stocks like Apple, Nvidia, and Microsoft weighing down the index and the Cboe Volatility Index reaching its highest level in nearly a month.
title: Iran-Israel conflict: Oil jumps 4%, markets on edge

description: Summer monsoon in India ended with above normal rainfall. IMD forecasts La Nina conditions forming by October-November, suggesting a potential harsh winter for north and northwest India, including Delhi-NCR. The true severity of the winter will be determined later as La Nina strengthens. The IMD will provide a more accurate forecast in November.
title: This winter may be harsh in North India due to La Nina conditions: IMD

description: The Supreme Court of India is set to draft guidelines for bulldozer actions against encroachers on public land, applicable nationwide and across all communities. The guidelines will ensure demolitions follow municipal laws without prior notice and prohibit targeting individuals solely based on criminal involvement, emphasizing a secular, fair approach to law enforcement.
title: SC: We won’t allow ‘bulldozer justice’ for alleged crime

description: Four days before Haryana polls, the state's BJP government granted a 20-day parole to Dera Sacha Sauda head Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh, permitting him to stay only at the Baghpat ashram in Uttar Pradesh. This move has sparked controversy due to its timing and potential influence on voters.
title: Ahead of Haryana polls, BJP govt grants Dera chief parole

description: A man entered a Shamli bank claiming he had a heavy debt and threatened to kill himself or the manager if not given Rs 40 lakh. The manager, fearing for his life, complied and handed over the money. Police are investigating, but formal complaints are yet to be received from the bank.
title: UP man walks into bank with suicide note, leaves with Rs 40 lakh

description: India's govt is expanding the 'trusted source' mandate from CCTVs to other segments like smart meters and drones, aiming to reduce dependency on Chinese imports and strengthen cybersecurity. Certification of key components is mandated to build a secure supply chain and prevent vulnerabilities.
title: Chinese smart meters, PCs may face security check

description: Sonam Wangchuk, along with 173 others advocating for Ladakh's inclusion in the Sixth Schedule, was detained by Delhi Police at the Singhu border. They began an indefinite hunger strike in protest. Political leaders and supporters condemned the detentions, calling for the protection of Ladakhi cultural identity.
title: Sonam Wangchuk & 170 others detained, go on fast

description: Nine police officers in Uttar Pradesh's Mirzapur district were suspended after a man was shot dead during a clash over a donation box for a local temple. The suspended officers had previously ignored complaints about ongoing disputes. Four suspects have been arrested, and investigations are ongoing to identify further involvement in the incident.
title: All 9 cops at UP thana suspended after man’s killing

description: Army chief General Upendra Dwivedi has described the Line of Actual Control situation as stable yet sensitive and not normal, stressing the Army's preparedness. Trust, he said, has been the biggest casualty amidst China's continuous military presence and reluctance to disengage troops in eastern Ladakh.
title: LAC situation 'stable but sensitive': General Upendra Dwivedi
‘Love jihad’ has foreign funding links, says judge, sends man to jail

description: Delhi high court has mandated social media platforms to present their SOPs and timelines for handling information requests from law enforcement. The court emphasized the need for adherence to proper timelines to prevent delays in tracing missing persons, including minors, and requested Delhi police to outline their challenges.
title: HC asks social media firms to provide SOPs for police information pleas

description: Polling in Jammu and Kashmir ended smoothly with no major law and order incidents, boasting high voter turnout and extensive candidate participation. The Election Commission highlighted significant increases in turnout, the peaceful nature of elections, and notable seizures to curb money and muscle power.
title: J&K elections: Nefarious intent defeated, says EC on peaceful polls

description: Manipur's ethnic conflict has escalated due to false narratives, including unfounded claims of drone bombings and militants from Myanmar. Army chief Gen Upendra Dwivedi highlights the need to control misinformation and support displaced civilians while addressing weaponisation and restoring trust.
title: Manipur a 'war of narratives' now: General Upendra Dwivedi

description: Following Iran's missile attacks on Israel, airlines like Lufthansa and SWISS are rerouting flights to avoid conflict zones, causing delays and cancellations. Air India and Opsgroup report increased GPS jamming and spoofing in the region, with pilots relying on alternative navigation methods for safety. Operations in the Middle East now require heightened vigilance and route adjustments.
title: Amid West Asia conflict, airlines decide not to overfly Iran, Iraq & Jordan

description: Babar Azam announced his resignation from the Pakistan men's white-ball cricket team captaincy to prioritize his performance and personal life. He expressed gratitude for the support received, emphasizing his anticipation to contribute as a player without the additional captaincy responsibilities.
title: Babar Azam resigns from Pakistan cricket team white-ball captaincy

description: Iran fired over 100 missiles at Israel, causing nationwide air raid sirens and prompting citizens to take shelter. The attacks heightened regional tensions, and in Amman, Jordan, the night sky was filled with missiles, while explosions were heard in the distance.
title: Watch: Air raid sirens sound across Israel as Iran strikes with wave of missiles

description: Iran launched a barrage of rockets, including ballistic missiles, near Tel Aviv in retaliation for Hezbollah chief Hassan Nasrallah's assassination. Israel deployed its Iron Dome defense system and urged citizens to seek shelter amid sirens and explosions. Over 100 missiles were launched in the joint attack by Iran and Hezbollah.
title: Iran attacks Israel to avenge Nasrallah's killing: What we know so far

description: Noida International Airport is set to commence commercial operations on April 17 next year, handling both domestic and international flights. Despite attempts to advance the date, any delay could push approvals and scheduling by six months. Flight trials by major airlines and necessary tests are scheduled in the upcoming months.
title: First flight to take off from Noida airport on April 17

description: The Israeli military confirmed the targeted killing of Muhammad Jaafar Qasir, a key Hezbollah commander responsible for weapons transfers from Iran to Lebanon. His death deals a significant blow to Hezbollah's logistics network and missile capabilities. Israel remains on high alert, anticipating potential retaliatory strikes from Hezbollah amidst escalating regional tensions.
title: Israeli military announces assassination of key Hezbollah weapons commander

description: Israeli authorities are investigating a suspected terror shooting in Tel Aviv near Jaffa, which left several casualties and at least four people critically injured. Emergency services are attending the scene amid rising regional tensions. More details are expected as the investigation continues and security forces remain on high alert.
title: Mass shooting in Israel's Tel Aviv kills 4

description: Bigg Boss 18, hosted by Salman Khan, reveals its list of 17 contestants including popular TV actress Alice Kaushik and Nia Sharma. Nia, confirmed by Rohit Shetty, prepares for the show with well-wishes from Abhishek Kumar and Bharti Singh. The show promises an electrifying season ahead.
title: Pandya Store fame Alice Kaushik confirmed to enter Bigg Boss 18

description: India set a new Test match record with a combined run-rate of 7.36 against Bangladesh in Kanpur. This broke South Africa's previous record of 6.80. India's victory came without facing a single maiden over, achieving multiple unprecedented milestones. They easily chased a target of 95 runs to secure the win.
title: India make history as first team to achieve...

description: In 1978, US-India relations strained due to Jimmy Carter's stern stance on nuclear fuel safeguards, resulting in a diplomatic rift that lasted two decades. Despite this, Carter held personal affection for India, actively supporting humanitarian projects and India's international aspirations well into his post-presidency years.
title: Old Man and the C: Jimmy Carter makes it 100 hoping to vote for Kamala on November 5

description: Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh, the chief of Dera Sacha Sauda, has been granted parole just before the Haryana Assembly polls. This decision was recommended by the Chief Electoral Officer of Haryana after a report from state authorities and a request for emergency parole. The assembly polls are scheduled for October 5.
title: Dera chief Ram Rahim Singh gets parole ahead of Haryana elections

description: Prashant Kishor, set to launch his political party in Bihar, questions CM Nitish Kumar's fitness for leadership, suggesting BJP props him up for its own gains. Kishor alleges BJP’s political strategies harm Bihar and predicts BJP’s downfall, asserting his party will offer a viable alternative focused on education and employment.
title: Prashant Kishor claims Nitish not 'physically & mentally' fit, says BJP will suffer for imposing him

description: Avoiding onions and garlic during Navratri offers various health benefits that extend beyond spiritual observance. From improved digestion and balanced body temperature, these dietary restrictions align with both physical well-being and spiritual growth. While not all dietary practices are universally accepted, the choice to abstain from these ingredients during such a sacred time can provide significant advantages.
title: 5 benefits of avoiding onion and garlic during Navratri

description: The JD Vance vs Tim Walz debate promises to be an intense and unfiltered verbal clash with significant implications for the upcoming presidential race. Vance, a skilled speaker with a compelling rags-to-riches story, appeals to a new generation of MAGA supporters and has experience handling hostile media. Walz, on the other hand, embodies a Midwestern, ‘America’s Dad’ persona, connecting with potential Democrats beyond coastal areas and showcasing strong liberal credentials.
title: America’s Dad vs Hillbilly Hope: What to expect from Vance and Walz debate

description: Derrick Anderson, a Republican congressional candidate in Virginia, faces criticism after posing in campaign photos with a friend's wife and children, implying they were his own. The Democratic Congressional Campaign Committee accused him of deceitful tactics to mislead voters about his family status.
title: Derrick Anderson poses for ‘happy family’ pics — with friend’s wife and kids

description: Prince William made an Instagram post just hours before Prince Harry's UK event. Reports claimed that Instagram post was made to overshadow Harry's UK return though William's friends have denied any links between the two. Harry's former bodyguard Ken Wharfe said Harry was always the more popular one among the two and William was jealous of him since childhood.
title: Harry is like mother Diana, William always jealous: Ex-bodyguard

description: A photo of IIT Bombay professor Chetan Singh Solanki wearing torn socks at a luxury hotel in New Delhi has sparked a conversation about sustainability. Solanki, known as the "Solar Man of India," explains that his choice aims to reduce waste and promote efficient resource use.
title: Why photo of IIT professor's 'torn socks' went viral

description: A 23-year-old Chinese man was taken into custody after injuring three children with a knife at a day-care facility in Zurich's Oerlikon district. The incident occurred around 12:00pm local time, and police are yet to disclose details about the attacker's identity and the children's injuries.
title: Zurich knife attack: Three children injured, Chinese man arrested
Debt-ridden men plotted Gujarat train derailment to rob passengers

description: Post Xi’s economic stimulus package, stocks of top luxury companies, most of which are European, are on the upswing. Because China accounts for a quarter of global luxury sales. But the question is whether what Xi has done is enough.
title: Xionism In Lux: Why global luxury biz bosses will obsess over China’s communist boss

description: Elon Musk and Vinod Khosla clashed over Argentina’s economy, with Musk siding with President Javier Milei’s policies. Khosla's incorrect unemployment figure led to a heated exchange, further fueled by media highlighting Argentina's rising poverty under Milei.
title: Musk calls Vinod Khosla 'dumb' in Twitter feud over Argentina’s economy

description: The Mysuru Urban Development Authority (MUDA) has decided to revoke the allocation of 14 plots to Chief Minister Siddaramaiah's wife, Parvathi B M, after she opted to relinquish them. This move follows an Enforcement Directorate (ED) inquiry into alleged irregularities. Parvathi cited her husband's respect and peace of mind as reasons for her decision.
title: MUDA agrees to take back plots allotted to Siddaramaiah's wife

description: Karan Veer Mehra won Khatron Ke Khiladi 14. He shared thoughts on Asim Riaz, who responded with a cryptic tweet. Riaz had issues with contestants and producers, leading to his exit. Celebrities and fans are divided, with some supporting and others criticizing Riaz. Krishna Shroff and Gashmeer Mahajani were runners-up.
title: 'The loser...' : Asim Riaz takes a jibe at Khatron Ke Khiladi 14 winner

description: Vaibhav Suryavanshi, a 13-year-old cricket sensation, made headlines by smashing a record-breaking century in just 58 balls during an unofficial U-19 Test against Australia. This remarkable feat, with 14 fours and four sixes, positions him among India's promising talents. Despite narrowly missing an overall U-19 Test record, his inspiration stems from cricket legend Brian Lara.
title: 13-year-old Vaibhav hits fastest hundred for India in U-19 Tests

description: WWE announced the Royal Rumble 2025, set in Indianapolis, on February 1, sparking speculation about John Cena's potential participation. His appearance could kickstart his 'Farewell Tour,' make the event grander, and possibly set up his final Championship run, aiming for a record 17th title win, which 'The Champ' richly deserves.
title: 3 Reasons why John Cena should participate in the 2025 Royal Rumble match

description: Russian heavyweight boxer Arslanbek Ruslanovich Makhmudov amazed the internet by wrestling with a bear in the forest, a spectacle watched by entertained spectators. His Instagram post, showing the unique face-off, went viral with over 12 million views and 300k likes, sparking varied reactions from users.
title: 'Citizenship test': Video of Russian boxer wrestling with bear goes viral

description: Customs officials at Delhi's IGI Airport have arrested a woman for attempting to smuggle 26 iPhone 16 Pro Max devices from Hong Kong. Valued at over Rs 37 lakh, the phones were concealed in a vanity bag. The woman has been booked under the Customs Act and investigations are ongoing.
title: Woman arrested for smuggling 26 iPhone 16 Pro Max: How she hid them

description: Bill Belichick, legendary NFL coach, has teamed up with Nike to support collegiate lacrosse programs, marking a significant shift from his past comments about Tom Brady's running skills in the sport. This partnership underscores Belichick's commitment to promoting lacrosse, America’s fastest-growing sport, reflecting his broader passion for athletic development beyond football.
title: Bill Belichick leaves Tom Brady jokes behind to join Nike in boosting lacrosse

description: Scientists from India's PRL and ISRO have confirmed that Chandrayaan-3 landed in a buried impact crater on the Moon. This ancient crater, possibly older than the South Pole Atkin basin, contains deeply excavated materials. The findings come from images captured by Chandrayaan-3 and Chandrayaan-2's navigation and high-resolution cameras.
title: Chandrayaan-3 landed in one of Moon’s oldest craters, Isro scientists claim discovery

description: India's Venus Orbiter Mission (VOM), carrying 19 scientific instruments including international payloads, is scheduled for a March 29, 2028 launch. The mission aims to explore Venus's atmosphere, surface, and Sun interaction, while demonstrating advanced ISRO technologies, with findings to be shared globally.
title: Venus orbiter to carry 19 payloads, take 112 days to reach orbit; launch in 2028

description: LOT Polish Airlines did not have any wheelchair on board as it's not their policy. BBC war correspondent Frank Gardner who is paralyzed had to crawl on his back to the washroom because of this policy. He posted his photo on X triggering a debate on how inhumane the airline policy is. Gardner, however, said the cabin crew were very helpful and apologetic.
title: Disabled UK journalist forced to crawl to flight bathroom

description: The debate over establishing five primary Test venues in India intensifies after rain disrupts a Test match. Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma offer differing perspectives on centralizing venues. Ashwin highlights the benefits of having multiple centers but refrains from endorsing a limited venue approach.
title: Kohli, Rohit, Ashwin offer differing vies on five Test centres

description: China's 75th anniversary of Communist rule was marked quietly amid fears of a Soviet-style collapse. President Xi Jinping emphasizes party loyalty and ideological discipline, wary of vulnerabilities like economic stagnation and public discontent. Xi’s focus on control and suppression highlights concerns over China’s economic future and the CCP's long-term stability.
title: 75 yrs of Communist Party rule: Can Xi help avoid a Soviet-style collapse?

description: The National Pension System (NPS) mandates a minimum annual contribution for Tier I accounts to remain active. If not met, accounts are frozen and require back payments plus a penalty for reactivation.
title: This is the minimum contribution needed to keep NPS account active

description: Using the Apple Find My feature, police in Connecticut tracked down and recovered a 2023 Ferrari worth $575,000 that was stolen and located AirPods inside it.
title: How Apple AirPods helped man find stolen Ferrari worth Rs 4.8 crore

description: Junior doctors in West Bengal resumed their indefinite protest, alleging the state failed to ensure safety in hospitals and quick justice for a murdered colleague. Their demands include the removal of the health secretary, increased hospital security, and accountability for administrative corruption. The protest has disrupted healthcare services, compelling senior doctors to cover essential duties.
title: RG Kar case: Junior doctors resumes protest accusing Bengal govt failed to fulfill demand

description: Absenteeism is rising globally, driven by post-pandemic health concerns, mental health issues, and poor working conditions. Tesla’s Berlin plant saw 17% of its workforce call in sick, prompting extreme measures. Burnout, stress, and shifting work-life balance priorities are significant factors. Employers can reduce sick leave by prioritizing employee well-being, improving conditions, and offering remote work flexibility.
title: Why do employees tend to take more sick leaves these days?

description: IMD reports the 2024 monsoon season concluded with 7.6% more rainfall than normal, impacting regions like Rajasthan, Gujarat, and Maharashtra. Predictions indicate above-normal rainfall for central and southern peninsular India from October to December, with above-normal temperatures expected for most parts of the country in October.
title: IMD reports 7.6% more rainfall during this year's monsoon

description: The BCCI enforces strict protocols for IPL players, banning those who withdraw after being picked in the auction for two seasons and mandating overseas players to register for the Big Auction to be eligible for subsequent auctions, to curb selective participation and withdrawals.
title: IPL: BCCI's stern message to overseas players

description: Union minister Chirag Paswan stated his willingness to resign if reservations or the Constitution are tampered with, aligning with his father's vision. He later clarified that his comments were directed at the UPA, not the current administration. Paswan praised PM Modi's government for addressing Dalit issues and confirmed his commitment to the NDA.
title: Chirag Paswan says he wouldn't hesitate to give up ministerial post if ...

description: Haryana Congress has petitioned the Election Commission of India to prevent the parole of Gurmeet Ram Rahim, the head of Dera Sacha Sauda, amid concerns that he might influence voters in the upcoming state assembly elections. They cited the ongoing model code of conduct as a reason to halt his temporary release.
title: 'May influence voters': Congress writes to EC on Ram Rahim's parole timing

description: Navratri 2024, from October 10 to 18, is dedicated to celebrating different forms of goddess Durga. Each day has a designated color symbolizing various qualities, such as yellow for happiness and red for strength. These colors play a vital role in the festival, reflecting devotion and enhancing the celebratory spirit.
title: Navratri colours 2024: Know the colour for each day of the Shardiya Navratri

description: India's captain Rohit Sharma shared insights on the team's dynamic under new head coach Gautam Gambhir after a strategic win in Kanpur's second Test against Bangladesh. The team adopted an aggressive approach on Day 4, leading to a 7-wicket victory. Key performances included Akash Deep’s impressive bowling, positioning India well for the upcoming Border Gavaskar Trophy against Australia.
title: 'I've played with him and know...': Rohit on Gambhir

description: Kendra Wilkinson has recently apologised for her comments about Sean "Diddy" Combs' infamous parties following his arrest. She clarified that she had been discussing her experiences at the Playboy Mansion when she unintentionally mentioned attending some of Combs' gatherings. Although she stated she hadn’t witnessed anything problematic, Wilkinson expressed her regret and hoped for justice for any victims involved. Meanwhile, Sean Combs, also known as P Diddy, faces multiple felony charges, including sex trafficking, drug possession, and firearms offences, following his arrest on 16 September. Denied bail, Combs remains in custody as serious allegations, spanning years, continue to emerge, with his legal team maintaining his innocence.
title: Why this playboy model had to apologise for her Diddy comments

description: A malicious app named WalletConnect – Airdrop Wallet on Google Play, disguised as a legitimate tool for Web3 apps, evaded detection for over five months, stealing $70,000 in cryptocurrency. The app deceived users by mimicking legitimate platforms and manipulating search rankings with fake positive reviews, achieving over 10,000 downloads before being removed.
title: Android users, delete this ‘dangerous’ crypto app from your phones

description: October 2024 will be exciting for Indian auto enthusiasts with major launches including Kia's electric SUV EV9, luxurious Carnival MPV, and Mercedes-Benz's E-Class. Nissan introduces the updated Magnite, while BYD unveils the eMax 7 electric MPV. These launches promise innovation, sustainability, and luxurious options, hinting at the future of driving in India.
title: Upcoming car launches in India: Kia EV9, BYD eMax 7, and more

description: Martin elaborated on the rationale behind this decision, drawing parallels with other iconic artists. He noted, “There’s only seven Harry Potters. There’s only 12 ½ Beatles’ albums; there’s about the same for Bob Marley, so all our heroes." This reference highlights how influential figures in music and literature have also set limits on their creative output, thereby enhancing the significance of their work.
title: Coldplay as a band to retire after 12th album, Chris Martin confirms

description: India secured a 2-0 series win against Bangladesh, with throwdown specialist Raghavendra Dwivedi awarded the series trophy. Former coach Ravi Shastri praised Raghu's crucial role in preparing Indian batters. Despite early struggles, Raghu's dedication paid off, leading to his invaluable presence in the Indian cricket team, culminating in the team's triumph.
title: Meet India's staff who was handed trophy after B'desh series win

description: Samajwadi Party MP Awadesh Prasad criticized BJP as DNA evidence in the Ayodhya rape case cleared SP leader Moeed Khan but implicated his domestic help, Raju Khan. The incident, involving a 12-year-old girl and political tensions, saw Moeed's bakery demolished. The DNA report's revelation intensified political debates, with upcoming bypolls adding significance.
title: 'CM Yogi's mindset towards Muslims ...': Faizabad MP hits back at BJP in Ayodhya rape case

description: Israel intensified its ground invasion preparations by targeting Hezbollah weapon facilities in southern Lebanon. The IDF's 98th Division, having gained experience in Gaza, is now conducting localized operations. Concurrently, airstrikes in Beirut targeted Hezbollah's military infrastructure.
title: Watch: IDF prepares for localised ground invasion in southern Lebanon

description: Ravichandran Ashwin acknowledges the benefits of limited Test centres, referencing Australia and England's approach, but refrains from recommending it for India, citing it as beyond his purview. He highlights the importance of diverse venues in fostering nationwide cricket talent and developmental opportunities.
title: 'Above my pay grade': Ashwin on if India should follow fewer Test centres model

description: The Bombay high court confirmed the death penalty for Sunil Rama Kuchkoravi, convicted of murdering his mother and frying her organs in 2017. The court upheld the 2021 trial court decision, citing the case as the 'rarest of rare' deserving capital punishment, with forensic evidence and eyewitness testimonies supporting the verdict.
title: Bombay HC confirms death penalty for man who killed mother, fried organs

description: A Delhi consumer court ordered Etihad Airways to pay Rs 75,000 for misplacing a passenger's check-in baggage and returning it after several days. The complainant alleged loss of valuable items, but the court found no merit in this claim due to undeclared items at the airport. The passenger's bag was misplaced and relocated during flight layovers from Sweden to Delhi.
title: Etihad Airways fined Rs 75k for delayed return of passengers’ lost baggage

description: Young Indian opener Yashasvi Jaiswal excelled in the second Test against Bangladesh, earning the 'player of the match' title. His impressive scores of 72 and 51 helped secure a seven-wicket win for India. At 22, Jaiswal surpassed Sunil Gavaskar's record for most runs by an Indian under 23, amassing 929 runs in 2024.
title: Jaiswal breaks Gavaskar's record, equals Sehwag's feat in Kanpur Test

description: West Bengal Governor CV Ananda Bose has requested a report from Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee on the utilization of Rs 1.17 lakh crore central funds allocated for 2023-24, highlighting issues of fiscal deficit, rising debt, and delayed CAG reports submission to the assembly.
title: Bengal governor asks Mamata for details of Rs 1.17 lakh cr central fund utilisation

description: New income tax laws grant companies extra time to deposit TDS, extending the deadline from 60 to 80 days after the original due date. Companies that fail to deposit the TDS by the return filing deadline will receive immediate prosecution notices. Employees are advised to monitor their Form 26AS for TDS credit validation.
title: Should employees be worried about new TDS deposit rules?

description: With the fourth and fifth retention coming at a premium, not many teams, maybe except Mumbai Indians, would look to exercise that option ahead of the mega auction
title: Mumbai Indians the winners under new IPL retention rule

description: In response to increased demand, the US Mission to India has announced 250,000 additional visa appointments for tourists, skilled workers, and students. This expansion aims to ease interview access and strengthen US-India ties, addressing the surging interest among Indian citizens to visit or relocate to the US.
title: US eases visa access for Indian students, workers and tourists

description: Chennai Super Kings CEO Kasi Viswanathan says they might not use the uncapped player rule for MS Dhoni and will have more clarity in the coming week
title: IPL: CSK to connect with MS Dhoni in 'coming week'

description: Iran’s Supreme Leader, Ali Khamenei, recently claimed on X that "Hezbollah is the victor," but Community Notes contributors quickly refuted this, pointing out Hezbollah's leadership losses in Israeli strikes. Among those killed were Sheikh Hassan Nasrallah, the group’s Secretary-General, and several other high-ranking leaders like Nabil Kaouk, Ibrahim Kobeissi, and Ibrahim Aqil. This series of airstrikes in 2024 has significantly weakened Hezbollah's leadership and capabilities. Elon Musk praised Community Notes for fact-checking Khamenei's claim. The system, launched in 2021 as Birdwatch and rebranded in 2022, relies on volunteers to provide accurate context to misleading posts.
title: Iran Supreme Leader tweeted 'Hezbollah is the victor'. It didn't age well...

description: The Bombay high court has confirmed the death sentence for Sunil Kuchkoravi, convicted of murdering his mother in 2017 and engaging in cannibalism. The judges deemed the crime as one of the 'rarest of rare' cases, highlighting the extreme brutality and danger posed by the convict.
title: Bombay HC upholds death sentence for man who killed and ate mother's body

description: Rahul Gandhi accused Prime Minister Narendra Modi of establishing a system that benefits a select few, allowing them to spend exorbitant amounts on weddings while farmers struggle under debt. Gandhi criticized Modi for allegedly favoring industrialists like Ambani and Adani over common citizens, arguing that such actions undermine the Constitution and harm the nation's employment system.
title: 'Whose money was it?': Rahul points to Ambani wedding to target PM Modi

description: Taylor Swift missed two consecutive Kansas City Chiefs games, fueling breakup rumors with Travis Kelce due to a viral 'break-up contract' dismissed as fake. Kelce addressed performance concerns on his podcast, emphasizing his focus on winning. Speculation persists online, although both parties allegedly remain amicable and committed to personal growth.
title: Taylor Swift's absence from Chiefs games has sparked speculation about her breakup

description: Rohit Kumar Singh, an IIT alumnus and retired IAS officer, shared his nostalgic journey from a job offer at TCS with a salary of Rs 1,300 per month to a ₹2,200 per month job in Indian Civil Services. His decision to prioritize public service over financial gain has garnered admiration on social media.
title: IITian who gave up TCS job to join civil services, shares TCS offer letter

description: India bolstered their quest for a spot in the World Test Championship final with a commanding 7-wicket win over Bangladesh in Kanpur, extending their lead at the top of the standings. This victory enhances their chances ahead of the upcoming series against New Zealand and Australia. Australia are second-best placed in the WTC standings with eight wins, three losses and a draw on 90 points and 62.50 points percentage.
title: How India can qualify for WTC final after Bangladesh series win

description: The Lucknow bench of the Allahabad High Court summoned an FSDA officer to explain the presence of banned Chinese garlic in Indian markets. This follows a PIL by Motilal Yadav, who presented both Chinese and Indian garlic in court. India banned Chinese garlic imports in 2014 due to health concerns, yet smuggling continues.
title: When garlic hit gavel: A spicy day in Lucknow courtroom

description: Delhi chief minister Atishi has claimed that police, on LG VK Saxena's orders, blocked her from meeting detained Ladakh climate activist Sonam Wangchuk. Atishi emphasized that this kind of governance is dictatorial and called for full statehood status for Ladakh and Delhi. Wangchuk long with 150 Ladakhis, has been detained since Monday night for allegedly violating prohibitory orders.
title: Atishi claims LG directed police not to let her meet Sonam Wangchuk

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah defends against corruption allegations after his wife Parvati surrendered 14 MUDA compensation plots gifted by her brother. He refutes claims of nepotism and maintains innocence, stressing that his wife's decision was to avoid political controversy and psychological distress.
title: Siddaramaiah brushes off allegations after wife decides to return MUDA plots

description: The Andhra Pradesh government has suspended the SIT probe into the Tirupati laddu 'prasadam' case till October 3. The decision follows a Supreme Court hearing that questioned the state's claim of using contaminated ghee without solid evidence. The court stressed that faith matters should remain outside the realm of politics. ​It sought answers from the state govt and TTD on how they came to the conclusion that contaminated ghee was used to make the laddus.
title: Andhra govt suspends SIT probe into Tirupati laddu case till Oct 3

description: India triumphed over Bangladesh by 7 wickets in Kanpur, sweeping the series 2-0 and solidifying their lead in the WTC standings. Dominated by Ashwin, Jadeja, and Bumrah's bowling, India chased a target of 95 runs efficiently, despite two rain-curtailed days. Rishabh Pant did the honours in the end, clearing the boundary rope with ease to seal the victory, which looked an improbable outcome after two washout days. Virat Kohli occupied the other end, remaining unbeaten on 29.
title: India wallop Bangladesh by 7 wickets, clinch series 2-0

description: A security flaw in Kia's 'Kia Connect' system, discovered by Sam Curry, exposed millions of cars made after 2013 to cyberattacks. Hackers could control critical functions remotely using a car's license plate number. Kia promptly fixed the issue after being notified.
title: Hackers could unlock your Kia car with just a license plate: Is yours safe?

description: Delhi Police's latest social media campaign uses the popular 'Ganji Chudail' meme to promote helmet safety. The post, featuring the animated character wearing a helmet, conveys the message to fear injury more than the witch, advocating for helmet use.
title: Delhi Police has a 'Ganji Chudail-inspired' warning for you
Several feared dead in school bus fire in Thailand

description: A Bengaluru resident thwarted a scam attempt by a fake Flipkart delivery man posing as an iPhone 15 delivery executive. He recorded the interaction and refused to accept the package without inspection, prompting the imposter to flee.
title: iPhone 15 scam: How a Bengaluru man caught fake Flipkart delivery man

description: Opposition leaders, including Mallikarjun Kharge and Arvind Kejriwal, criticize the BJP for detaining environmentalist Sonam Wangchuk and 150 volunteers. They were detained while marching to Delhi to voice concerns and demand government dialogue on Ladakh's ecological and tribal issues.
title: 'Cowardly', 'undemocratic': Oppn leaders slam detention of Sonam Wangchuk

description: Fresher hiring in India's IT sector is set to double in fiscal year 2025, driven by demand in the BFSI segment and large deal wins. Companies like TCS, Infosys, and Wipro are resuming campus hiring with significant commitments.
title: Good news for freshers! Indian IT sector entry-level hiring set to double in FY25

description: The Supreme Court of India reiterates that mere accusations or convictions cannot justify property demolitions, emphasizing uniform legal standards for all communities. The court mandates a notice period before demolition and disapproves of using bulldozers as punitive measures, stressing the need for judicial oversight to prevent misuse.
title: 'Because somebody is an accused or convict, it can't ... ': SC on bulldozer action

description: Shark Tank India returns with its fourth season, featuring new hosts Sahiba Bali and Ashish Solanki. The show continues to showcase innovative business ideas, with Sharks like Anupam Mittal and Aman Gupta returning with fresh looks. Expect new dynamic sharks and captivating entrepreneurial pitches.
title: Shark Tank India 4: Sharks begin shooting for the new season

description: Actor Rajinikanth was hospitalized in Chennai due to stomach ache and unerwent  a cardiologist-recommended procedure. Post-surgery, he is stable and under special care for 2-3 days. His wife Latha assures that all is well. Rajinikanth is currently involved in projects 'Coolie' and 'Vettaiyan'.
title: Rajinikanth health update: Stent placed in lower abdomen, discharge in 3 days

description: A Flipkart delivery man was killed in Lucknow while attempting to deliver an iPhone.
title: Man orders iPhone with CoD option on Flipkart, kills delivery agent

description: Virat Kohli's aggressive demeanor and formidable batting against Australia have defined India's competitive rivalry with them. His confrontations with players like Mitchell Johnson, especially during the 2014 Border-Gavaskar series, were marked by verbal spats and intense on-field battles, solidifying Kohli as a key figure in these iconic encounters. The battles between Johnson and Kohli remain an iconic chapter in India-Australia cricket history.
title: When Virat Kohli-Mitchell Johnson confrontation elevated the intensity

description: India will observe Gandhi Jayanti on October 2, 2024. Several state-specific holidays will also cause banks to be closed for up to 15 days in October.
title: Are banks in India closed on Oct 2? Check bank holidays list

description: Mussoorie's streets came to a standstill as 71 Lamborghinis in various models and colors paraded through the town, capturing attention from residents, tourists, and shopkeepers. The spectacular convoy, part of the Lamborghini Giro 2024 event, stopped traffic and was widely filmed by onlookers.
title: Watch: Lamborghini parade lights up Uttarakhand's Mussoorie

description: Bangladesh's stubborn resistance was finally broken by Jasprit Bumrah just before lunch, as he dismissed Mushfiqur Rahim with a clever off-cutter. Bangladesh was bowled out for 146, leaving India to chase a modest target of 95 for victory.
title: Watch: Bumrah ends Bangladesh resistance with a peach of a delivery

description: A deputy director of a Ministry of Defence training institute had her iPhone 15 Pro snatched by two bike-borne men in South Delhi's Lodhi Colony. The incident left her injured and concerned about her professional data. Police are investigating the case using CCTV footage.
title: Robbers snatch iPhone of defence ministry institute's official in Delhi

description: Army Chief Upendra Dwivedi stated that the situation along the LAC in eastern Ladakh is stable but sensitive. He highlighted positive diplomatic signals aimed at resolving the standoff with China but emphasized that ground decisions rely on military commanders. Full resolution is needed to return to the pre-April 2020 situation. India insists on disengagement for normal ties.
title: 'Trust biggest casualty': What Army chief said on LAC standoff with China

description: Tech companies continue significant layoffs in 2024, with IBM, Microsoft, and Cisco majorly affected. IBM's cuts focus on senior roles while Microsoft reduces its gaming division. Cisco plans a 7% workforce reduction. Smaller firms like Dozee and WeTransfer also face job losses. This indicates ongoing restructuring in the tech industry.
title: Tech layoffs cross 1 lakh: Cisco, Microsoft cut more jobs in September

description: The National Investigation Agency (NIA) conducted coordinated raids on 12 locations in West Bengal, targeting individuals suspected of Maoist links. The raids were carried out across various locations including Netaji Nagar, Panihati, Barrackpore, Sodepur, and Asansol, in connection with the alleged involvement of two women and their associates with Maoists,
title: NIA raids 12 locations across West Bengal over Maoists links

description: Ahead of the IPL 'Big Auction,' franchises prepare to announce retained players. Each can keep up to six, with a limit on capped and uncapped players. Mohammad Kaif emphasizes retaining KKR captain Shreyas Iyer for his leadership in their championship win, alongside players like Phil Salt, Andre Russell and Sunil Narine.
title: IPL Retention: KKR advised by Kaif to first retain... - Watch

description: Investors are shifting from India's overvalued market to China, following Beijing's major stimulus measures. China's stock indices have surged, while Indian markets face selling pressures and foreign outflows.
title: ‘Buy China, Sell India’? China’s big stimulus makes FIIs pull away from stock markets

description: Former Delhi deputy CM Manish Sisodia criticized the BJP for poor road conditions while highlighting Arvind Kejriwal's commitment to making Delhi pothole-free. Current CM Atishi, along with AAP leaders, conducted inspections to prioritize road repairs, with responsibilities assigned to various leaders for different districts.
title: BJP has dug potholes everywhere to trouble Delhi people: Sisodia

description: The Patel and Mavalankar families in Ahmedabad exhibit extraordinary dedication to blood donation, with combined contributions of nearly 986 liters. The Patels have donated 630 liters, while the Mavalankars have given 356 liters, showcasing a multi-generational commitment to ensuring a steady blood supply for those in need.
title: This Patel family of Ahmedabad has donated 630 litres of blood!

description: Govinda reacts to getting shot by his own revolver. The actor has sent a voice note for his fans, thanking the doctors who removed his bullet. The actor is now safe but has injured his leg and lost some blood.
title: Govinda reacts to getting shot by his own revolver, expresses gratitude to fans

description: Rajinikanth's health is stable and he will return home soon after the completion of medical treatment.
title: Rajinikanth hospitalised in Chennai

description: Senator JD Vance's comparison of abortion to slavery has fueled criticism from reproductive rights advocates. During his campaign, Vance has promoted a nationwide abortion ban and voiced support for federal measures to limit access. Kamala Harris has strongly criticized Vance’s views and their potential implications.
title: JD Vance draws comparison between 'abortion' & 'slavery' in resurfaced audio clip

description: A US company's HR team faced a shakeup after a manager discovered a flaw in the ATS system that incorrectly filtered qualified candidates. A fake resume submitted by the manager exposed the software's error, leading to the dismissal of half the HR department for missing this critical issue affecting the hiring process.
title: Why this US-based IT company fired its entire HR team

description: Water supply in parts of west Delhi will be disrupted for 16 hours on October 1-2 due to major repair work at the Haiderpur Water Treatment Plant, affecting areas such as Varun Niketan and Raja Garden. Residents are advised to store sufficient water and may request water tankers if needed.
title: Water supply to be hit in parts of Delhi today and tomorrow; check details here

description: Govinda got shot accidently with his own gun as he was about to leave for Kolkata from Mumbai. The actor is currently in the hospital and recuperating as the doctors have removed the bullet.
title: Govinda's accidental bullet injury: Here's what exactly happened

description: In October 2024, different zodiac signs will experience varied financial outcomes. Aries will see unexpected gains from investments, while Gemini should avoid impulsive spending. Taurus and Cancer benefit from real estate, and Leo should monitor expenses post-19th. Scorpio faces increased spending, and Pisces must reassess their spending habits.
title: Monthly Money Horoscope, October 2024

description: PlayStation gamers encounter widespread outages affecting multiple consoles including PS4, PS5, and PS Vita. The disruptions have led to errors in loading systems, and the PSN Service Status page confirms issues with launching games, apps, and network features. Sony is working to resolve the problem.
title: PlayStation down: Sony confirms the outage, says ‘working to resolve the issue'
LPG price hike: 19kg commercial gas cylinders costlier by Rs 48.50

description: Mount Everest's increasing height is attributed to the isostatic rebound caused by the merger of the Kosi and Arun rivers about 89,000 years ago. According to their estimates, isostatic rebound is responsible for approximately 10% of the yearly uplift rate of Everest. Isostatic rebound is a geological phenomenon that is not limited to the Himalayan region.
title: Why Mount Everest is growing taller every year

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah supports his wife Parvati's decision to return 14 compensation plots amidst a land allotment controversy. Siddaramaiah accuses opposition parties of false complaints to incite political hatred and vows to fight legally against corruption charges. He acknowledges his wife's psychological distress but respects her decision.
title: 'Suffering psychological torture': Siddaramaiah on wife's choice to return MUDA plots
Actor Govinda accidentally gets shot in the leg, rushed to hospital

description: On October 1st, 2024, numerology influences suggest different energies for each number. Number 1 individuals should embrace creativity and leadership, while Number 2 may need patience and guidance. Number 3 find introspection helpful, and Number 4 focus on organization. Numbers 5 through 9 deal with charm, reality checks, heightened emotions, financial planning, and dynamic energy respectively.
title: Numerology predictions today: Read for numbers 1 to 9

description: India's cricket team has adopted a flexible and aggressive batting approach, differing from England's 'Bazball' strategy. This has led to more successful counter-attacks and fewer collapses. Batters like Yashasvi Jaiswal and Shubman Gill exemplify this by adapting to conditions before hitting aggressively, making India's all-format batting lineup hard to plan against.
title: Rohit Sharma & Co. unleash India's own brand of attacking Test batting

description: Pakistan's Test captain Shan Masood defended his player and opening batsman Abdullah Shafique, highlighting his superior Test records over Virat Kohli's early career, amidst criticism of the squad's selection. The media questioned Masood and PCB's selection of players, pointing out the inconsistency in the team's performance over a period of time.
title: 'Abdullah Shafique's record is better than Virat Kohli'

description: Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath called Rahul Gandhi an 'accidental Hindu' raised in Roman culture, contrasting him with PM Modi who embraced Ram's culture. He criticized Congress for not supporting the Ram Mandir's construction and accused the party of undermining Sanatan culture and constitutional institutions.
title: Accidental Hindus raised in Roman culture can't accept Ram temple: Yogi

description: Junior doctors in West Bengal have resumed an indefinite strike over safety concerns, following the rape and murder of a colleague. The protest, lasting 52 days, demands government action on security. Senior doctors and civil society organisations are organising rallies in Kolkata, pressing for justice and governmental intervention to ensure medical staff safety.
title: Kolkata rape-murder: Bengal junior doctors resume 'total cease work'

description: The Israel Defense Forces launched a ground invasion into southern Lebanon targeting Hezbollah’s military infrastructure near the border. This follows two weeks of airstrikes, with the goal of neutralizing immediate threats to Israeli communities. Hezbollah vows to confront Israeli troops, marking potential for intensified ground engagement.
title: Operation 'Northern Arrows': Israel begins ground raids in Lebanon, eye on Hezbollah bases

description: Dallas Cowboys’ key linebacker DeMarcus Lawrence is set for injured reserve, joining teammates Anthony Brown and Jaylon Smith. The team is evaluating options, including promoting DE Carl Lawson, to fill the gap. Lawrence, since his 2014 draft, has been crucial with an average of 54 tackles and 7.4 sacks per season, making his absence significant.
title: DeMarcus's injured reserve placement forces Dallas to make adjustments

description: In a major move, Sebi proposed expanding T+0 settlement from 25 to 500 stocks to enhance liquidity. The regulatory board approved 'Investment Strategies' for high-net worth individuals and 'MF Lite' for passive investments. Streamlined rights issue processes and eased regulations for investment advisers were also sanctioned.
title: Liquidity boost: Sebi steps up same-day stock settlement

description: RBI deputy governor Swaminathan J has urged small finance banks to evaluate their reliance on high-cost deposits for long-term stability and warned against imposing high interest rates and fees on borrowers. He emphasized the need for SFBs to promote inclusive growth through innovative technology and improve grievance redressal mechanisms, highlighting some concerning practices within the sector.
title: RBI cautions small financial banks on FDs

description: Pakistan Test captain Shan Masood's press conference saw an awkward moment when a journalist's question prompted intervention from Pakistan Cricket Board's media director, Sami ul Hasan. Concern over Masood and his team's performance underlined recent criticism of the PCB and selectors following poor results, such as the recent 0-2 Test defeat by Bangladesh.
title: 'Pakistan ka captain hai, show respect': Drama at press conference!

description: Lucknow Police have revealed the murder of e-commerce delivery boy Bharat Kumar, who was killed by two youths for refusing to hand over COD phones without payment. Akash Kumar has been detained while the search for accomplices Gajanand and Himanshu continues, with police and SDRF teams combing the canal for the victim's body.
title: No cash to pay for high-end phones, 2 kill delivery boy in Lucknow

description: Security forces in Bastar's Sukma district uncovered a Maoist hideout, discovering a TV set among the propaganda and daily use items. This rare find has puzzled authorities, speculating its purpose might have been for entertainment. Other recovered items include a gun and explosives. Further investigation is needed to determine the TV's origin and use.
title: ‘Jugaad to pass time': Security forces find TV set in Bastar Maoist hideout

description: Superstar Rajinikanth, 73, was admitted to Apollo Hospital for an elective cardiac procedure. His condition is stable. Fans eagerly await updates while looking forward to his film 'Vettaiyan', releasing on October 10, 2024, featuring an impressive cast and music by Anirudh Ravichander.
title: Superstar Rajinikanth admitted to a Chennai hospital

description: Using its extraordinary power under Article 142 of the Constitution, the Supreme Court has ensured admission for a talented Dalit youth at IIT-Dhanbad by creating an additional seat, after he missed the fee deadline. The court emphasized the importance of providing such opportunities to deserving students.
title: Admit Dalit student who failed to arrange fee in time: SC to IIT

description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar will visit Colombo this week for the first high-level engagement with newly elected President Anura Kumara Dissanayake. The visit aims to reaffirm India's commitment to Sri Lanka amid concerns over potential shifts in foreign policy under the Marxist leadership.
title: Jaishankar to visit Sri Lanka this week, first by any EAM since prez poll

description: Manufacturing in India has bounced back strongly from the Covid-19 impact, reflecting a 7.4% rise in GVA for 2022-23 and industrial output surging over 21%. Employment and wages have also improved, surpassing pre-pandemic levels. Key growth drivers include basic metals, petroleum, food, chemicals, and vehicles, contributing significantly to the sector's output.
title: In FY23, manufacturing jobs rise 7.6%, wages up 5.5%: Govt survey

description: The Nagpur bench of Bombay HC acquitted a 64-year-old man convicted of raping an eight-year-old, citing that the minor's behavior did not align with the trauma expected in such cases. The court also noted inconsistencies in the mother's and the child's testimonies.
title: HC acquits man of raping minor as 8-year-old was not 'petrified'
